<package name="viddy" project="openSUSE:Factory">
  <title>A modern watch command</title>
  <description>Modern watch command.
Features:
* Basic features of original watch command:
  + Execute command periodically, and display the result.
  + color output.
  + diff highlight.
* Time machine mode:
  + Rewind like video.
  + Go to the past, and back to the future.
* See output in pager.
* Vim like keymaps.
* Search text.
* Suspend and restart execution.
* Run command in precise intervals forcibly.
* Support shell alias
* Customize keymappings.
* Customize color.

</description>
  <devel project="utilities" package="viddy"/>
  <url>https://github.com/sachaos/viddy</url>
</package>
